I think the pattern's difficulty feels fine but my main worry is that at 01:14:542 - the same violin notes that elexire maps out at 01:16:256 - onwards come in, and since they stick out more than the trilled violin notes I'm mapping I feel like they wouldn't blend in with elexire's part due to that jacky pattern being a lot harder than 01:16:256 - 

(though part of the reason is because my brain likes the symmetry between 01:13:685 - and 01:14:542 - lmao)

huh I never noticed that sound lmao

I'll keep this open since I want to playtest this warm on Monday but if I add it in I'm thinking of turning 00:55:470 (55470|1,55470|0) - into a [13] double and placing the note at 00:55:379 - on 2

ofc my big concern is keeping *some* kind of break after 00:55:256 (55256|3) - so I really don't want 00:55:379 - on the same hand as 00:55:170 (55170|3,55170|2,55256|3) - , but if the [13] double/note on 2 idea feels good to play to me then I'm cool with applying it!

ye tags probably optional, though always nice to add if possible (dq would b minor one for bn evals aka it means nothing)

the hs thing tho lets just wait till mapper comes and gives their thoughts
lets make it middle and put 7.8 :D

aaaa I thought about doing that when I first mapped it but I didn't really like how 2-1 into a [12] double felt there. the current pattern sacrifices consistency a bit but I think it feels a lot better to play
keep一下 我觉得是这样隔断打起来舒服点

ok mb, more than half it is. 

those were just the vibes i was getting from the one-liners sry if i was wrong
02:23:992 and 02:33:592 should have similar sv structure with sv resets no?

55% definitely not a "most", defensiveness? I'm just responding based on maps I've seen from the same artist in the current ranked section

Don't get me wrong I don't mind if the mapper wants to DQ because of these "simple thing" , I can just re-nom later rq. Is it wrong for me to respond with what I thought was true to the map that I nominated?
vocal ends on red tick and its better to put spacing on downbeat in my opinion
current rhythm works great with vocals and emphasize drums at the same time so prefer to keep it

hmm I think I'd prefer to keep those as is. I guess it's pretty subjective but I feel like 00:26:081 (26081|3,26135|1,26188|0) - sounds about as intense at all 3 notes, it's just that the kicks at 00:26:028 (26028|1,26028|0) - and 00:53:456 (53456|0,53456|1) - are really loud (and I kind of prefer the current pattern flow-wise when playtesting)
vocal feels held here and no finisher so keep
